criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  meet the referral criteria for bariatric surgery;

          -  BMI >40 kg.m-2 or >35 kg.m-2 with obesity-related comorbidities;

          -  Motivation to participate in the study, regardless to the allocation group

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  use of drugs that interfere with bone metabolism (i.e. bisphosphonates, teriparatide,
             calcitonin, hormone replacement therapy, chronic use of corticosteroids, thiazide
             diuretics);

          -  Unable to perform exercise of moderate intensity;

          -  Health condition that could be aggravated by exercise (i.e. uncontrolled arterial
             hypertension, severe kidney disease, class III New York Heart Association heart
             failure);

          -  Peri-menopausal status with last menstruation <1 year;

          -  Known metabolic bone disease (i.e. Osteogenesis Imperfecta, Paget bone disease);

          -  Concurrent participation in a structured exercise program (>30 min in duration >1
             day/week);

          -  Pregnancy or breast-feeding
